A woman ties "Rakhi" , a sacred thread, on the wrist of a man, on the occasion of Raksha Bandhan, in the outskirts of Agartala, India's northeastern state of Tripura, Aug. 3, 2020. Raksha Bandhan, meaning the bond of protection, is a festival to celebrate the relationship between brothers, cousins and sisters. At this festival, a sister ties a sacred thread on her brother's wrist, which symbolizes the sister's love and prayers for her brother's well-being, and the brother's lifelong vow to protect her. (Str/Xinhua)Â 

